snippet: Bernard Foley scored all but 5 of Australia’s points in a 33-13 win in London that ensured that England, the host team, would not advance out of the Rugby World Cup’s pool stage.
abstract: Australia beats England, 33-13, in Rugby World Cup match.
lead_paragraph: Bernard Foley scored all but 5 of Australia’s points in a 33-13 win in London that ensured that England, the host team, would not advance out of the Rugby World Cup’s pool stage.
